terms.term: Electronic Residency Application Service. AAMC system for applying to most residency programs.
Each medical student is submits a minimum of 3 and a maximum of 4 letters of recommendation to each of the residency programs they apply to.
Held on the Friday of the 3rd week in March. When all US seniors find out where they matched.
A minor wrongdoing. A crime that can be punished with a maximum of one year or less. In Ohio, speeding is considered a minor misdemeanor.
Medical Student Performance Evaluation, A letter of evaluation which describes the student's performance in medical school. It is released to residency programs on October 1st.
National Residency Matching Program: ERAS applicants and programs rank each other.
A 500 word or less statement that describes why a medical student is choosing theie residency specialty and allows the residency program director to learn more about them.
The practice of taking someone else's ideas and passing them off as one's own.
The number an accepted publication is given in the PubMed system.
